{#
  hx-meter — Drupal Twig Template
  =================================
  Scalar measurement gauge within a defined range. Renders a progress-bar
  style meter with semantic color feedback (optimum/warning/danger zones).

  Variables:
    - value    (number, required): Current value of the meter. Clamped to [min, max].
    - min      (number, optional): Minimum value. Default: 0.
    - max      (number, optional): Maximum value. Default: 100.
    - label    (string, optional): Visible label and accessible name for the meter.
               Required when no label slot content is provided. Healthcare context:
               use a meaningful description like "Disk usage" or "Patient risk score".
    - low      (number, optional): Threshold below which value is suboptimal.
    - high     (number, optional): Threshold above which value is suboptimal.
    - optimum  (number, optional): The optimal value. Used to determine which
               zone is "good" when combined with low/high thresholds.
    - attributes (object, optional): Additional Drupal attributes object.

  Semantic state (color feedback) is determined automatically:
    - No thresholds → default state (neutral color)
    - With thresholds, no optimum → 'optimum' (in range) or 'warning' (out of range)
    - With thresholds and optimum → 'optimum', 'warning', or 'danger' based on zone

  Usage:
    Simple disk usage meter (no thresholds):
      {% include 'hx-meter.twig' with {
        value: disk_used_percent,
        label: 'Disk usage',
      } %}

    Patient risk score with thresholds:
      {% include 'hx-meter.twig' with {
        value: risk_score,
        min: 0,
        max: 100,
        low: 30,
        high: 70,
        optimum: 10,
        label: 'Patient risk score',
      } %}

    Medication adherence (higher is better):
      {% include 'hx-meter.twig' with {
        value: adherence_pct,
        min: 0,
        max: 100,
        low: 50,
        high: 80,
        optimum: 100,
        label: 'Medication adherence',
      } %}

  Registration:
    Load the component script in your theme's .libraries.yml:
      hx-meter:
        js:
          path/to/@helixui/library/dist/hx-meter.js: { attributes: { type: module } }
#}

{% set _min = min|default(0) %}
{% set _max = max|default(100) %}

<hx-meter
  value="{{ value }}"
  min="{{ _min }}"
  max="{{ _max }}"
  {% if label %}label="{{ label }}"{% endif %}
  {% if low is defined and low is not null %}low="{{ low }}"{% endif %}
  {% if high is defined and high is not null %}high="{{ high }}"{% endif %}
  {% if optimum is defined and optimum is not null %}optimum="{{ optimum }}"{% endif %}
  {% if attributes %}{{ attributes }}{% endif %}
></hx-meter>
